  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>Prerequisites: The ability to cast at least one spell</em></p>\n<p>You have practiced casting spells in the midst of combat, learning techniques that grant you the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You have <strong>advantage </strong>on <strong>Constitution saving throws</strong> that you make to maintain your concentration on a spell when you take damage.</li>\n<li>You can perform the somatic components of spells even when you have weapons or a shield in one or both hands.</li>\n<li>When a hostile creature's movement provokes an opportunity attack from you, you can use your <strong>reaction </strong>to cast a spell at the creature, rather than making an opportunity attack. The spell must have a casting time of <strong>1 action</strong> and must target only that creature.</li>\n</ul>",
